319a23cB1620acf7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;"> a few days</a> to go through. If you send your b=
rokerage money on Monday, it might not have the money until Wednesday or so=
. If you send your brokerage $10,000 on Monday, though, it is extremely lik=
ely that you want to trade on Monday. And the brokerage wants you to trade =
when you want to trade, since (1) that is how it makes money and (2) that i=
s good customer service and keeps you coming back to trade more. So it is f=
airly common that, when you open a brokerage account and transfer in $10,00=
0, the broker will let you do $10,000 worth of trading right then. It will =
check your bank account, see the $10,000, see you start the transfer, figur=
e you=E2=80=99re almost certainly good for you, and float you the $10,000 t=
o start trading right away.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The obvious trade is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Buy $10,000 of out-of-the-money call =
options on volatile meme-y stocks with your $10,000 credit.</li>=09<li styl=
e=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Immediately take the $10,000 out of your bank acc=
ount so that the transfer to the brokerage never actually goes through.</li=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If the call options don=E2=80=99t pay=
 off, never mind, you got a free gamble.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">If the call options do pay off, you put the money back into your ban=
k account, say =E2=80=9Coops sorry mix-up at the post office,=E2=80=9D send=
 it back to the brokerage and collect your winnings. (Or, even better, you =
collect your winnings from the brokerage=C2=A0<em>without=C2=A0</em>ever se=
nding it the money in the first place. The timing on this is pretty tight, =
since you have to cash out before the brokerage notices that you never cash=
ed in, but not strictly impossible.)</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is, I must emphasize, a<em>=C2=A0</em>cri=
me, but it is sort of an obvious trade, and people do it, and the brokerage=
 expects a certain amount of it. It is kind of worth it, to the broker. If =
you show up at a brokerage and say =E2=80=9CI have=C2=A0money, I want to tr=
ade out-of-the-money options on meme stocks,=C2=A0and I would like to do th=
at as quickly as possible,=E2=80=9D the brokerage is=C2=A0<em>thrilled</em>=
. Selling options to impulsive buyers is the most lucrative possible busine=
ss for a retail brokerage, and they=E2=80=99ll do it all day long, and they=
 will extend credit and take credit risk to do more of it. If you do a ton =
of that business, 95% of the impulsive option buyers will make tons of mone=
y for you, and 5% will skip out on payments, and that mix of business is st=
ill just fine.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/29584608.276473/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzL=
XJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMi0xOTc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcec663a5" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> here=E2=
=80=99s this</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Monday=
] charged six individuals, including a federal inmate, for conducting a fre=
eriding scheme that defrauded multiple broker-dealers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC=E2=80=99s complaint alleges that from =
May 2019 to early January 2021, Syed Arham Arbab, 25, and five others made =
more than $2 million in bogus deposits from empty or underfunded bank accou=
nts into various brokerage accounts to deceive broker-dealers into providin=
g instant deposit credit for online securities trading. The complaint alleg=
es that Arbab and his fellow participants, which included his high school a=
nd college friends and a relative, received more than $1.5 million in insta=
nt deposit credit that they used to make unfunded online trades, which caus=
ed affected broker-dealers to lose at least $146,660. The complaint alleges=
 that, in some instances, Arbab=E2=80=99s co-defendants gave Arbab their br=
okerage account log-in credentials so that he could personally engage in fr=
eeriding using their accounts, while, in other instances, Arbab coached suc=
h individuals in real time through text messages about how to freeride usin=
g their own accounts. Arbab allegedly conducted this scheme just before sta=
rting his prison sentence for another securities related scheme. The SEC pr=
eviously charged Arbab in 2019 for running a Ponzi scheme from his fraterni=
ty house near the University of Georgia campus=E2=80=94for which he began s=
erving a five-year sentence in January 2021, after he pleaded guilty in a p=
arallel criminal case by the U.S. Attorney=E2=80=99s Office for the Middle =
District of Georgia.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I do not know if Arbab is a Money Stuff reader=
 but I do appreciate his curiosity and dedication to learning about financi=
al crime. Imagine getting that call from Arbab, like, =E2=80=9Chey I have f=
ound a good trade, you want in?=E2=80=9D If I were his friend getting that =
call, I might have said something like =E2=80=9Cwait aren=E2=80=99t you goi=
ng to prison for a Ponzi in like a month, are you sure you should be doing =
this?=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, to be fair, some did. From <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29584608.276473/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
c2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMi9jb21wLXByMjAyMi0xOTcucGRm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd82fb00c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the SEC complaint</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In August 2019, principally using online text =
messages and social media messaging, Arbab began soliciting friends and acq=
uaintances in multiple<br />states=E2=80=94many current or former students =
he knew from UGA=E2=80=94to engage with him in free-riding online using dif=
ferent brokers=E2=80=99 trading platforms.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arbab described the free-riding in various mes=
sages as =E2=80=9Ca way to trade without capital.=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arbab provided a succinct description of the s=
cheme, which he explained allowed him to make money at the expense of broke=
r-dealers whom he called =E2=80=9Cbig corporations=E2=80=9D for whom he had=
 =E2=80=9Cno remorse.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arbab solicited at least two dozen individuals=
 to join him in his free-riding scheme.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Of these, many individuals declined Arbab=E2=
=80=99s solicitation.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But not everyone!</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On March 11, 2020, four days after Arbab had s=
igned a settlement with the SEC in his previous Ponzi-scheme litigation, Mc=
Kinney received a text from Arbab containing Arbab=E2=80=99s multi-step scr=
ipt on how to free-ride in a brokerage account. Arbab urged McKinney to fre=
e-ride in McKinney=E2=80=99s brokerage account at BD 1, texting him: =E2=80=
=9C[d]on=E2=80=99t tell anyone about this [because] this is what I=E2=80=99=
ve been doing =E2=80=A6 to scalp a few thousand[.]=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">McKinney responded to Arbab, texting back: =E2=
=80=9CHoly [s---] that sounds risky [a[s] f---].=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arbab responded: =E2=80=9CYou don=E2=80=99t ne=
ed the money that=E2=80=99s the thing . . . You=E2=80=99re borrowing it all=
 from [BD 1].=E2=80=9D ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">McKinney subsequently emptied his bank account=
 at Arbab=E2=80=99s instruction and initiated a $5,000 deposit from the sam=
e bank account into his BD 1 brokerage account.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When the $5,000 deposit posted the next day on=
 March 12, 2020, McKinney=E2=80=99s bank account that was linked to his BD =
1 account had a balance of $0, as McKinney had moved $1,281.18 out of his b=
ank account just before he and Arbab began free-riding.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Before the $5,000 deposit reversed for insuffi=
cient funds on March 17, 2020, Arbab =E2=80=93 using McKinney=E2=80=99s acc=
ount log-in credentials provided by text message =E2=80=93 and McKinney =E2=
=80=93 taking instructions from Arbab via text =E2=80=93 each used McKinney=
=E2=80=99s BD 1 account to submit various trades, making a total of $17,551=
.16 of purchases and $19,243.73 of sells in TSLA and TWTR call options, and=
 McKinney was able to successfully withdraw $1,701.32 in profits.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After this withdrawal, McKinney was enthusiast=
ic about continuing to free-ride with Arbab, texting to Arbab: =E2=80=9CAre=
 we doing the same thing again tomorrow?=E2=80=9D to which Arbab replied: =
=E2=80=9CYessir.=E2=80=9D McKinney then responded: =E2=80=9CHell yea.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">His friends allegedly vouched for him, both to=
 other participants:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around this time, on March 15, 202=
0, at Arbab=E2=80=99s request, McKinney individually texted a separate indi=
vidual who lives in Texas to vouch for Arbab=E2=80=99s free-riding, writing=
: =E2=80=9CHey =E2=80=A6 It=E2=80=99s blake one of Syed=E2=80=99s friends. =
Not gonna lie dude knows how to hustle. I=E2=80=99d be lying if I said I di=
dn=E2=80=99t make ~ $1700 in profits in one day with his help.=E2=80=9D The=
 individual in Texas subsequently gave Arbab control of his brokerage accou=
nt for trading.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And=C2=A0to the judge sentencing him for his o=
ther crimes:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On February 19, 2020, Rahman submi=
tted a letter to the sentencing judge in Arbab=E2=80=99s criminal Ponzi sch=
eme case, urging the judge to be lenient in Arbab=E2=80=99s sentencing. Rah=
man wrote, in part, that Arbab =E2=80=9Cshouldn=E2=80=99t have to be locked=
 up in prison for such a long time for a mistake that cannot compare to all=
 the ways he is able to benefit society.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I mean definitely one way he can benefit socie=
ty is by teaching other people how to do financial crimes, though I am not =
sure that=E2=80=99s a=C2=A0<em>net=C2=A0</em>benefit.</p>
